# Cursor Team Kit

This repo is set up to use every **Cursor Team Kit** plugin skill and the **ci-watcher** subagent. Prefer invoking them instead of reimplementing their behavior.

## Skills to invoke

- **check-compiler-errors** — Run `npm run typecheck` (or `npm run build`) and report failures. Use before or with fix-ci.
- **deslop** — Remove AI slop and tidy code style when the user asks for cleanup or polish.
- **fix-ci** — When CI is failing: find the job, inspect logs, apply a focused fix.
- **fix-merge-conflicts** — When there are merge conflicts: resolve non-interactively, validate build/tests, finish resolution.
- **get-pr-comments** — When the user wants a summary of review comments on the active PR.
- **loop-on-ci** — When the user wants CI to pass: watch runs and iterate until all checks pass.
- **new-branch-and-pr** — When the user wants a new branch, work completed, and a PR opened.
- **pr-review-canvas** — When the user pastes a GitHub PR URL or asks to "review this PR": generate the interactive PR review.
- **review-and-ship** — When the user wants a full review, key issues fixed, and changes shipped via PR.
- **run-smoke-tests** — When the user wants to run or fix Playwright smoke tests (`npm run test:e2e`).
- **weekly-review** — When the user wants a weekly summary of their commits (bugfix, tech debt, new work).
- **what-did-i-get-done** — When the user wants a summary of their commits over a given time period.

## Subagent

- **ci-watcher** — Use when waiting for CI results or when CI has failed; use proactively to monitor branch CI.

## Plugin rules (automatic)

The plugin enforces:

- **no-inline-imports** — Imports at top of file only.
- **typescript-exhaustive-switch** — Exhaustive switch for TS unions/enums.

No extra configuration needed; follow these by default.
